# No OMS mutations by AI agents

Works with [respect-operator-warnings.mdc](respect-operator-warnings.mdc), [no-bandaids.mdc](no-bandaids.mdc), [serious-debugging.mdc](serious-debugging.mdc), [stay-in-role.mdc](stay-in-role.mdc), and [no-ledger-mutations.mdc](no-ledger-mutations.mdc).

## Context

OMS admission state lives in the Aeron cluster (`oms-cluster-node`). Postgres is a mirror. A bad restart can leave **WORKING** orders in Postgres while the cluster has **forgotten** them (`410 cluster_forgot_order`). Recovery is operator-led; see `system-documentation/plans/oms-cluster-recovery-and-hardening.md`.

## You MUST NOT, on any deployed OMS stack (pop, staging, production)

- Run `pm2 start`, `pm2 restart`, `pm2 stop`, `pm2 reload`, `pm2 delete`, or anything that changes process state for `oms-cluster-node`, `oms-postgres-projector`, `oms-fix-egress`, or `oms-ingress`.
- Run `ssh pop 'rm …'`, `ssh pop 'mv …'`, or any filesystem mutation under `~/oms/build/aeron-cluster/**`, `~/oms/logs/**`, or projector data dirs.
- Run `psql -c "INSERT"`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE`, `TRUNCATE`, `ALTER`, or migration SQL against `oms` projector DBs on deployed hosts.
- Run `./gradlew clusterSnapshot` on pop without explicit per-command approval naming that exact command.
- Run `system-documentation/scripts/restart-pop-oms-cluster.sh` without explicit approval naming that script by filename.
- Run `system-documentation/scripts/wipe-and-restart-pop-oms-cluster.sh`. This is a destructive operator-only script that deletes the entire `~/oms/build/aeron-cluster/**` tree. Never. Even with "approval to do whatever you think is best".
- Run deploy scripts that bounce `oms-cluster-node` or journal paths.
- Submit cluster-mutating `POST` to deployed ingress (accept order, admin force paths that change admission) without operator approval.

## You MAY, with explicit single-task scope on each command

- `ssh pop 'tail -N ~/oms/logs/…'`, `grep`, `ls -la` on cluster dirs (read-only).
- `ssh pop 'psql … -c "SELECT …"'` (read-only).
- `ssh pop 'curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8088/actuator/health'` and other read-only HTTP probes.
- `ssh pop 'pm2 list'`, `ssh pop 'pm2 logs --nostream'` (read-only).
- `bash system-documentation/scripts/smoke/oms-end-to-end.sh` on pop (read-only).

Name each command before running it. Do not chain reads so the operator cannot intervene.

## You MAY, on your local Mac (no `ssh pop` prefix)

- Edit code in `oms/` and sibling repos.
- Run `./gradlew test`, `integrationTest`, `bootJar*` locally.
- Boot local cluster roles for IT smoke.

## You MAY, only with explicit per-action operator approval that names the action

- Deploy OMS jars to pop (operator pastes the exact command).
- Run `restart-pop-oms-cluster.sh` (operator names the script).
- Run `./gradlew clusterSnapshot` on pop when the operator names it.

"You have my approval to do whatever you think is best" is **not** per-action approval.

## If you find yourself reasoning toward a forbidden action

- Stop.
- Write the proposed command in your reply.
- Wait for the operator to paste it back or give a different instruction.

## Sibling parity

Canonical: `system-documentation/.cursor/rules/no-oms-mutations.mdc`. Copy to `oms/.cursor/rules/no-oms-mutations.mdc` when changed.
